The paper discusses the use of reinforcement learning and planning for sequential decision making problems, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also proposes the use of a latent variable model to represent valid states, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper evaluates its method on image-based tasks, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV).
